sequenceDiagram
    autonumber

    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API Server<br/>6443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Webhook as KServe Webhook<br/>9443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Controller as KServe Controller Manager
    participant Knative as Knative Serving
    participant StorageInit as Storage Initializer<br/>(Init Container)
    participant CloudStore as Cloud Storage<br/>(S3/GCS/Azure/HF)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Gateway as OpenShift Gateway<br/>/ Istio Ingress<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant ModelPod as Model Server Pod<br/>8080/TCP
    participant Client as External Client

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over User,ModelPod: Flow 1: InferenceService Deployment (Serverless Mode)
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply InferenceService<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (kubeconfig)
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /validate-...-inferenceservice<br/>Auth: Client Certificate, TLS 1.2+
        Webhook-->>K8sAPI: Validated + Defaulted
        K8sAPI-->>User: InferenceService created

        Controller->>K8sAPI: Watch event received
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create Knative Service<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute / VirtualService<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

        Knative->>K8sAPI: Create Pod with init containers
        K8sAPI->>Webhook: POST /mutate-pods<br/>Auth: Client Certificate
        Note over Webhook: Injects storage-initializer,<br/>kserve-agent sidecar

        StorageInit->>CloudStore: Download model artifacts<br/>Auth: Cloud credentials, TLS 1.2+
        CloudStore-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts
        Note over ModelPod: Model server starts<br/>with downloaded model
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client,ModelPod: Flow 1 (continued): Inference Request
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/{model}:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer Token, HTTPS/443
        Gateway->>ModelPod: Forward request<br/>8080/TCP HTTP (pod-internal)
        ModelPod-->>Gateway: Prediction response
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over User,ModelPod: Flow 2: LLMInferenceService Multi-Node Deployment
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply LLMInferenceService<br/>Auth: Bearer Token

        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create LeaderWorkerSet<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create HTTPRoute<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create DestinationRule<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create InferencePool + InferenceModel<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceMonitor + PodMonitor<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

        Note over Client,ModelPod: LLM Inference Request
        Client->>Gateway: POST via HTTPRoute<br/>Auth: Bearer Token, HTTPS/443
        Gateway->>ModelPod: Via InferencePool scheduler<br/>Self-signed TLS
        ModelPod-->>Gateway: LLM Response
        Gateway-->>Client: Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 240, 255)
        Note over User,CloudStore: Flow 3: Local Model Caching
        User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply LocalModelCache<br/>Auth: Bearer Token

        Note over Controller: kserve-localmodel-controller
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create PV / PVC<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create/Update LocalModelNode<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token

        Note over Controller: kserve-localmodelnode-agent (DaemonSet)
        Controller->>K8sAPI: Create download Job<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
        StorageInit->>CloudStore: Download model to local PV<br/>Auth: Cloud credentials, TLS 1.2+
        CloudStore-->>StorageInit: Model artifacts → local storage

        Note over ModelPod: InferenceService pod<br/>mounts local PVC<br/>(zero cold-start)
    end
